{"title":"AnalisisCriticoPapers iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica/AnalisisCriticoPapers iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Analisis Critico de Papers","guid":"","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"PREGUNTA DE INVESTIGACION","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"PICO → estructura obligatoria","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"P = Poblacion → quien se estudia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"Criterios de inclusion y exclusion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"Representatividad de la muestra","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"Donde son extrapolables los resultados","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"2","text":"I = Intervencion → que se evalua","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"Farmaco, procedimiento, estrategia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"Dosis, duracion, forma de administracion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"2","text":"C = Comparador → contra que se compara","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Placebo, tratamiento estandar, no intervencion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"Comparador ACTIVO vs PASIVO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"2","text":"O = Outcome (Desenlace) → que se mide","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"PRIMARIO → potencia estadistica calculada para este","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"Secundarios → accesorios, sin potencia suficiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"Desenlaces duros vs surrogados","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"Pregunta bien formulada → estudio bien disenado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"0","text":"TIPO DE ESTUDIO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Jerarquia de evidencia (piramide)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"IDEAL → Ensayo clinico randomizado doble ciego (RCT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"Ensayo clinico no randomizado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"19","text":"Estudio de cohortes (prospectivo > retrospectivo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"19","text":"Estudio de casos y controles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"19","text":"Estudio transversal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"19","text":"Series de casos y reportes de casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"19","text":"Opinion de expertos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"18","text":"Metanalisis y revisiones sistematicas → sintesis de RCTs","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"PRISMA → guia de reporte de RS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"Heterogeneidad (I2) → >50% significativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"27","text":"Funnel plot → evaluar sesgo de publicacion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"18","text":"Estudios observacionales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"STROBE → guia de reporte","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"No permiten causalidad, solo asociacion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"31","text":"Utiles cuando RCT no es etico o factible","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"35","parent":"0","text":"VALIDEZ INTERNA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Definicion → grado libre de ERROR SISTEMATICO (sesgo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"EVALUACION DE CALIDAD METODOLOGICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Score de JADAD (escala 0-5)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Item 1 → estudio descrito como randomizado (0-1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"Item 2 → estudio descrito como doble ciego (0-1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"Item 3 → descripcion de perdidas y retiros (0-1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"Bonificacion (+1) si randomizacion apropiada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"38","text":"Bonificacion (+1) si cegamiento apropiado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"38","text":"Penalizacion (-1) si randomizacion inapropiada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"38","text":"Penalizacion (-1) si cegamiento inapropiado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"38","text":"Score >=3 → calidad aceptable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"38","text":"LIMITACION → concordancia interobservador moderada (kappa 0.37-0.39)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"37","text":"Cochrane Risk of Bias (RoB 2.0) → preferido actualmente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Dominio 1 → proceso de randomizacion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Dominio 2 → desviaciones de intervencion asignada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"Dominio 3 → datos de outcome faltantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"Dominio 4 → medicion del outcome","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"48","text":"Dominio 5 → seleccion del resultado reportado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"48","text":"Juicio → bajo riesgo, algunas preocupaciones, alto riesgo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"37","text":"JBI Critical Appraisal Tools","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Checklists especificas por tipo de estudio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"Cuasi-experimentales, cohortes, transversales, etc","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"37","text":"Newcastle-Ottawa Scale (NOS)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Para estudios observacionales (cohortes, casos-controles)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"3 dominios → seleccion, comparabilidad, outcome","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"37","text":"GRADE → calidad de evidencia para recomendaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Alta, moderada, baja, muy baja","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"Factores que bajan → sesgo, inconsistencia, imprecision, indirectness","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"61","text":"Factores que suben → efecto grande, dosis-respuesta, confusores residuales","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"35","text":"DOBLE CIEGO → LO MAS IMPORTANTE para validez interna","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"Participante no sabe que recibe","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"Investigador no sabe que administra","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"65","text":"Triple ciego → evaluador de outcomes tambien cegado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"65","text":"Previene sesgo de desempeno y deteccion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"35","text":"RANDOMIZACION","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Asignacion aleatoria → grupos comparables al inicio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"Elimina sesgo de seleccion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"70","text":"Ocultar secuencia de asignacion (allocation concealment)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"70","text":"Tipos → simple, bloques, estratificada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"70","text":"Verificar tabla de caracteristicas basales (Tabla 1)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"35","text":"SESGOS (amenazas a validez interna)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"Sesgo de seleccion","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"Berkson (admision hospitalaria)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"Neyman (prevalencia-incidencia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"77","text":"No respuesta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"77","text":"Voluntario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"77","text":"Perdidas de seguimiento → NO aleatorias","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"76","text":"Sesgo de informacion (medicion)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Clasificacion NO diferencial → atenua hacia nulidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Clasificacion diferencial → cualquier direccion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Sesgo de MEMORIA (recall bias) → casos recuerdan mas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"83","text":"Sesgo del entrevistador → conoce la condicion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"76","text":"Sesgo de CONFUSION (confounding)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"Confundente → asociado a exposicion Y a outcome","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"Confundente NO es paso intermedio en via causal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"Control → randomizacion, estratificacion, multivariado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"88","text":"Ejemplo clasico → tabaco confunde alcohol-cancer pulmon","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"35","text":"MANEJO DE PERDIDAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Analisis por INTENCION DE TRATAR (ITT)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"Analiza TODOS los randomizados, independiente de adherencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"Preserva efecto de randomizacion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"94","text":"Refleja efectividad en mundo real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"94","text":"Puede subestimar eficacia del tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"94","text":"ES EL ANALISIS PRIMARIO recomendado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"93","text":"Analisis POR PROTOCOLO (PP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Solo analiza los que completaron protocolo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"Refleja eficacia maxima del tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"Riesgo de sesgo → perdidas pueden ser sistematicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"100","text":"Util como analisis complementario","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"93","text":"Analisis de sensibilidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Evaluar impacto de diferentes supuestos sobre perdidas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"Peor escenario, mejor escenario, MICE","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"0","text":"VALIDEZ EXTERNA (generalizabilidad)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"Definicion → resultados aplicables a OTRAS poblaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"DEPENDE de la validez interna → sin esta, no hay externa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"Factores que afectan","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Criterios de inclusion-exclusion → muy restrictivos limitan","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Setting del estudio → monocentrico vs multicentrico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"Poblacion estudiada → edad, comorbilidad, etnia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"Intervencion → replicable en practica real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"111","text":"Seguimiento → duracion suficiente para outcomes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"117","parent":"108","text":"RESULTADOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"118","parent":"117","text":"Adherencia → alta adherencia en estudio vs mundo real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"117","text":"Tamano del efecto → NNT, NND, ARR, RRR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"117","text":"Intervalos de confianza → precision del estimado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"117","text":"Significancia clinica vs estadistica → p <0.05 no basta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"117","text":"Consistencia con otros estudios","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"108","text":"FINANCIAMIENTO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"SIEMPRE revisar quien financia el estudio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"123","text":"Conflictos de interes de autores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"123","text":"Industria farmaceutica → sesgo de publicacion positiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"123","text":"Estudios independientes → mayor credibilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"123","text":"Registro previo del protocolo → ClinicalTrials.gov, PROSPERO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"108","text":"Extrapolabilidad → donde aplican estos resultados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Edad de la muestra vs mi paciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Comorbilidades incluidas vs excluidas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"Contexto de salud → pais, sistema, recursos disponibles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"GERIATRIA → AM frecuentemente excluidos de RCTs","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"0","text":"ESTRUCTURA DEL PAPER","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"Titulo → refleja diseno y PICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"Abstract → estructurado (objetivo, metodos, resultados, conclusiones)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"134","text":"Introduccion → contexto, gap de conocimiento, pregunta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"134","text":"METODOLOGIA → seccion mas importante para lectura critica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"Diseno del estudio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"Poblacion y criterios de seleccion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"Intervencion y comparador","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"138","text":"Outcomes primario y secundarios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"138","text":"Tamano muestral y calculo de potencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"138","text":"Metodos estadisticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"138","text":"Aprobacion etica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"134","text":"Resultados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"Tabla 1 → caracteristicas basales (verificar balance)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"Flowchart CONSORT → flujo de participantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"146","text":"Outcome primario con IC 95% y valor p","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"146","text":"Outcomes secundarios → interpretar con cautela","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"146","text":"Analisis de subgrupos → solo exploratorios","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"134","text":"Discusion","guid":"","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"LIMITACIONES → OBLIGATORIO reconocerlas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Aumentan validez y transparencia del estudio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Identificar sesgos no controlados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"Discutir generalizabilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"152","text":"Comparacion con literatura previa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"152","text":"Implicancias clinicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"152","text":"Futuras investigaciones","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"134","text":"GUIAS DE REPORTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"CONSORT → RCTs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"160","text":"STROBE → observacionales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"160","text":"PRISMA → revisiones sistematicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"160","text":"STARD → estudios diagnosticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"160","text":"CARE → reportes de caso","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"0","text":"POTENCIA ESTADISTICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Definicion → probabilidad de detectar un efecto real (1-beta)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"Generalmente 80% o 90%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"166","text":"Calculada para el OUTCOME PRIMARIO unicamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"166","text":"Outcomes secundarios → SIN potencia suficiente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Resultados secundarios positivos → solo generan hipotesis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"No se pueden hacer conclusiones definitivas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"166","text":"Tamano muestral → determinado por calculo de potencia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"Efecto esperado, alpha, potencia deseada, variabilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"Considerar tasa de perdidas esperada (10-20% adicional)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"166","text":"Error tipo I (alpha) → falso positivo (generalmente 0.05)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"166","text":"Error tipo II (beta) → falso negativo (generalmente 0.20)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"166","text":"Subanalisis y multiplicidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"Correccion de Bonferroni → alpha/numero comparaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"178","text":"Ajuste por comparaciones multiples","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clinicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"JADAD >=3 necesario pero NO suficiente → usar RoB 2.0 como complemento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Doble ciego es LO MAS IMPORTANTE para validez interna","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Outcome primario = unico con potencia estadistica real","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"181","text":"Outcomes secundarios SOLO generan hipotesis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"181","text":"Analisis ITT preserva randomizacion → es el analisis preferido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"181","text":"SIEMPRE verificar quien financia el estudio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"181","text":"Tabla 1 del paper → primer lugar para evaluar randomizacion efectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"181","text":"CONSORT flowchart → ver perdidas y razones de exclusion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"181","text":"AM frecuentemente excluidos de RCTs → limita validez externa en geriatria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"181","text":"Significancia estadistica (p<0.05) NO implica relevancia clinica → buscar NNT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"181","text":"Un paper que reconoce sus limitaciones es MAS creible, no menos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"181","text":"Registro previo en ClinicalTrials.gov reduce riesgo de reporte selectivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIEN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"→ Validez y Sesgos en Investigacion (Metodologia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"→ Validacion de Instrumentos de Salud (Metodologia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"→ Estadistica Basica (Metodologia)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"1. Jadad AR et al. Assessing the quality of reports of RCTs: is blinding necessary? Control Clin Trials. 1996;17(1):1-12.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"2. Clark HD et al. Assessing the quality of randomized trials: reliability of the Jadad scale. Control Clin Trials. 1999;20(5):448-52.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"3. Sterne JAC et al. RoB 2: a revised tool for assessing risk of bias in randomised trials. BMJ. 2019;366:l4898.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"198","text":"4. Barker TH et al. The revised JBI critical appraisal tool for quasi-experimental studies. JBI Evid Synth. 2024;22(3):378-88.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"198","text":"5. Schulz KF et al. CONSORT 2010 Statement. Ann Intern Med. 2010;152(11):726-32.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"198","text":"6. Guyatt GH et al. GRADE: an emerging consensus on rating quality of evidence. BMJ. 2008;336(7650):924-6.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"198","text":"7. Moher D et al. CONSORT 2010 Explanation and Elaboration. BMJ. 2010;340:c869.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":205,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"AnalisisCriticoPapers iPad","id":"map_2298","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"AnalisisCriticoPapers iPad"}